{"name":"Mathlib.Algebra.LinearRecurrence","instances":[{"typeNames":["LinearRecurrence"],"name":"instInhabitedLinearRecurrence","className":"Inhabited"}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Data.Polynomial.Eval","Mathlib.LinearAlgebra.Dimension"],"declarations":[{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.lean#L220-L230","name":"LinearRecurrence.geom_sol_iff_root_charPoly","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.html#LinearRecurrence.geom_sol_iff_root_charPoly","doc":"The geometric sequence `q^n` is a solution of `E` iff\n`q` is a root of `E`'s characteristic polynomial. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.lean#L214-L215","name":"LinearRecurrence.charPoly","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.html#LinearRecurrence.charPoly","doc":"The characteristic polynomial of `E` is\n`X ^ E.order - ∑ i : Fin E.order, (E.coeffs i) * X ^ i`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.lean#L201-L203","name":"LinearRecurrence.solSpace_rank","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.html#LinearRecurrence.solSpace_rank","doc":"The dimension of `E.solSpace` is `E.order`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.lean#L179-L189","name":"LinearRecurrence.tupleSucc","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.html#LinearRecurrence.tupleSucc","doc":"`E.tupleSucc` maps `![s₀, s₁, ..., sₙ]` to `![s₁, ..., sₙ, ∑ (E.coeffs i) * sᵢ]`,\nwhere `n := E.order`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.lean#L159-L169","name":"LinearRecurrence.sol_eq_of_eq_init","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.html#LinearRecurrence.sol_eq_of_eq_init","doc":"Two solutions are equal iff they are equal on `range E.order`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.lean#L145-L155","name":"LinearRecurrence.toInit","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.html#LinearRecurrence.toInit","doc":"The function that maps a solution `u` of `E` to its first\n`E.order` terms as a `LinearEquiv`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.lean#L139-L140","name":"LinearRecurrence.is_sol_iff_mem_solSpace","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.html#LinearRecurrence.is_sol_iff_mem_solSpace","doc":"Defining property of the solution space : `u` is a solution\niff it belongs to the solution space. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.lean#L130-L134","name":"LinearRecurrence.solSpace","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.html#LinearRecurrence.solSpace","doc":"The space of solutions of `E`, as a `Submodule` over `α` of the module `ℕ → α`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.lean#L124-L126","name":"LinearRecurrence.eq_mk_of_is_sol_of_eq_init'","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.html#LinearRecurrence.eq_mk_of_is_sol_of_eq_init'","doc":"If `u` is a solution to `E` and `init` designates its first `E.order` values,\nthen `u = E.mkSol init`. This proves that `E.mkSol init` is the only solution\nof `E` whose first `E.order` values are given by `init`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.lean#L103-L118","name":"LinearRecurrence.eq_mk_of_is_sol_of_eq_init","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.html#LinearRecurrence.eq_mk_of_is_sol_of_eq_init","doc":"If `u` is a solution to `E` and `init` designates its first `E.order` values,\nthen `∀ n, u n = E.mkSol init n`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.lean#L95-L98","name":"LinearRecurrence.mkSol_eq_init","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.html#LinearRecurrence.mkSol_eq_init","doc":"`E.mkSol init`'s first `E.order` terms are `init`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.lean#L88-L91","name":"LinearRecurrence.is_sol_mkSol","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.html#LinearRecurrence.is_sol_mkSol","doc":"`E.mkSol` indeed gives solutions to `E`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.lean#L74-L84","name":"LinearRecurrence.mkSol","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.html#LinearRecurrence.mkSol","doc":"A solution of a `LinearRecurrence` which satisfies certain initial conditions.\nWe will prove this is the only such solution. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.lean#L68-L69","name":"LinearRecurrence.IsSolution","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.html#LinearRecurrence.IsSolution","doc":"We say that a sequence `u` is solution of `LinearRecurrence order coeffs` when we have\n`u (n + order) = ∑ i : Fin order, coeffs i * u (n + i)` for any `n`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.lean#L57-L58","name":"instInhabitedLinearRecurrence","kind":"instance","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.html#instInhabitedLinearRecurrence","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.lean#L54-L54","name":"LinearRecurrence.coeffs","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.html#LinearRecurrence.coeffs","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.lean#L53-L53","name":"LinearRecurrence.order","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.html#LinearRecurrence.order","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.lean#L52-L52","name":"LinearRecurrence.mk","kind":"ctor","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.html#LinearRecurrence.mk","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.lean#L52-L54","name":"LinearRecurrence","kind":"structure","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/LinearRecurrence.html#LinearRecurrence","doc":"A \"linear recurrence relation\" over a commutative semiring is given by its\norder `n` and `n` coefficients. "}]}